Description: AlulA is an aviation communications network allowing real time operational data to be collected radically cheaper than any other means.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: With just a few, cheap, tiny, crowd-sourced radio antennas, AlulA is fixing costly headaches and saving millions of dollars for an entire industry and its ever growing customer base. Passengers demand a lot from their airlines these days: zero tolerance for unexpected delays to the cheapest rate possible is becoming the norm. Customers are also hyper-informed about airlines' average delay times and comparative rates. And with new tools such as Google Flights for instance, they’re beginning to make decisions based on these facts. AlulA has developed a simple solution that can push the aviation industry closer to the Holy Grail: combining competitive airfares with happier customers, via fewer unexpected and expensive flight delays. Delays cost airlines, and therefore passengers a lot of money, time and frustration. The good news is: Many unexpected delays can be avoided, if only the right people had the right information to make critical decisions before critical failures occur. AlulA is taking advantage of the untapped potential of an existing global network of tiny antennas, which already exist in thousands of homes worldwide. Upgrading these inexpensive versions of large radio towers allows this network to collect valuable aircraft data from planes passing overhead. This crowd then forwards AlulA the data they collect, and enables AlulA to retrieve live aircraft health data. This then allows airplane maintainers to see problems starting to arise before they result in expensive component failure, which costs airlines upward of $8.00 a second, or nearly $30,000 an hour of downtime, and ultimately cost you the passenger higher average airfares and frustration of missing your connecting flight due to unexpected delays. AlulA’s mission is to provide a cost effective, universal solution for aircraft data streaming . AlulA offers a unique system to affordably broadcast aircraft data in real-time, which we refer to as beyond 4D (beyon4d).
Industry Groups: Hardware, Information Technology, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Software, Transportation

He has received many awards, including "Teacher of the Year" in 1990 (Desert Sands Unified School District, CA). He is a frequent speaker at educational conferences such as CABE (California Bilingual Education), and more recently at Techno-Caribe, Puerto Rico. RamÃ³n brings a fresh approach to today's educational challenges. As a result of his nearly 20 year teaching career (In Spain, The United Kingdom, and Los Angeles County, California), RamÃ³n experienced a need for uniform, easy-to-use computer software, which was both effective and affordable for teachers. He assembled a team of colleagues who joined the effort to make his vision a reality, and thus DownHill Publishing was founded. Primary projects RamÃ³n spends his time working on three innovative projects: developing high quality educational software, manufacturing revolutionary rear projection screens, and creating amusing Illuminated Manuscripts. 1.
